    <summary>A 3D visualization program for crystals and molecules.</summary>
    <description>
      VESTA is a 3D visualization program for structural models, volumetric data such as electron/nuclear densities, and crystal morphologies.
      VESTA supports a wide range of input and output formats, and aims to be fast and responsive.

      Read more about VESTA at the [official site](https://jp-minerals.org/vesta/en/download.html), or in the [original paper](http://scripts.iucr.org/cgi-bin/paper?S0021889811038970).

      # License

      This software is released under a noncommercial license, with two caveats:
        - Drawings produced by VESTA that end up in publications must be explicitly acknowledged.
        - Redistribution of files is prohibited without explicit written permission.
      For more information, see the official [license page](https://jp-minerals.org/vesta/en/download.html).

      This package is not affiliated with the authors of VESTA.

      # Installation Options

      Specify installation options using `choco install --params '/param1 /param2'`. Available parameters:
        - `/NoStart`: Don't install start menu shortcut. By default, a start menu shortcut is installed.
        - `/UserStart`: Install to user start menu instead of system start menu.
        - `/FileAssoc`: Associate VESTA with some of the most common file formats (.vesta, .cif, .pdb, .xyz, ...). By default no associations are made.
    </description>

